The Fractal Resonance Processor (FRP) repository contains the public simulation, documentation, and verification layer of the project.

The current FRP v0.9.3-mobile candidate is a Python simulation prototype of a ternary resonant coherence processor architecture.

It is not a hardware implementation.

Current results are limited to the documented Python simulation domain and do not represent hardware-validated performance, measured physical heat, measured electrical switching-energy reduction, or fabrication-level processor behavior.

